Tyrael: My group has suffered rather heavy casualties, and only three 
of us remain. There was also someone who did not seem of transformer 
origins allied with us. That one seems powerful, but he seems to have 
vanished for now. As for Megatron or Galvatron, my orders were to 
disable Megatron. There was no specification.

--- In nbwrpg@y..., Rudra656@a... wrote:
> ::Cygnar::
>        He lands on the island and transforms approaching the others. 
 "I'm 
> glad to see you have both made it here and aren't trying to kill 
each other.  
> It would crimp our working relationship if you were.  But now, we 
need to get 
> down to the business at hand.  We all have our separate reasons for 
being 
> here.  You, Rodimus want Galvatron dead.  And, you, Tyrael, want 
Megatron 
> dead.  I want them separated.  I would prefer Galvatron not die, but 
I am ... 
> flexible in that regard."  He looks between the two of them.  "We 
must 
> organize our forces quickly.  And effectively.  Are there any others 
you 
> think should participate in this attack?"
